title.narrative: By end 2022, key departments, public-sector institutions and stakeholders at national and provincial level have improved capacities to measure child poverty, increase public sector investments for children and design polices/programs and inclusive social protection systems by use of high-quality data, research and evaluative evidence.

description.narrative: Technical and research support informed key governmental strategies and C4D approaches for evidence-based gender-focused, child-centred social policy formulation including enhanced allocations for basic services. Strategic partnership with the Government and partners enabled UNICEF's engagement in the National Poverty Metrics Committee to influence child-centred poverty measurement. An integrated parenting package was developed to drive community-based care for early childhood development. Gender-mainstreaming, including support for menstrual hygiene management at school and public and religious debate empowered adolescent girls to reduce its stigma. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
